A grimy avantoe is a herb that has not yet been cleaned to make an avantoe. Grimy avantoes may be grown from an avantoe seed with a Farming level of 50. It is also dropped by certain NPCs. Cleaning a grimy avantoe requires a Herblore level of 48 and gives 10 Herblore experience. Clean avantoes are used to make fishing potions, super energy potions and hunter potions, requiring levels 50, 52, and 53 Herblore respectively.

Changes[edit | edit source]

Date Changes
12 August 2020
(update)

Composting grimy avantoe will now yield supercompost instead of regular compost.

9 March 2017
(update)

The item's value was increased from 1 to 18.

26 February 2015
(update)
  • The item was graphically updated to distinguish it from other grimy herbs.
  • The item was renamed from "Herb" to "Grimy avantoe".
  • The item was made tradeable on the Trading Post/Grand Exchange.
  • The “Identify” option was changed to a “Clean” option.
25 February 2013
(update)
  • The item was renamed from "Grimy avantoe" to "Herb".
  • The "Clean" option was changed to an "Identify" option.
22 February 2013
(update)
  • The item was renamed from "Herb" to "Grimy avantoe".
  • The "Identify" option was changed to a "Clean" option.
